00:51:30.270 --> 00:51:31.728
of a [? book, ?]
that I didn't talk

00:51:31.728 --> 00:51:34.650
about in this particular
talk, which is just

00:51:34.650 --> 00:51:36.950
around the
unresponsiveness of a lot

00:51:36.950 --> 00:51:38.730
of our political
institutions and the role

00:51:38.730 --> 00:51:40.800
that money plays in
politics and the revolving

00:51:40.800 --> 00:51:42.570
door between lobbyists
and legislators,

00:51:42.570 --> 00:51:45.042
and the rise of a
very complicated

00:51:45.042 --> 00:51:46.500
bureaucratic and
technocratic state

00:51:46.500 --> 00:51:47.610
which makes people
feel like nobody's

00:51:47.610 --> 00:51:48.568
